comments: After Porzingis (WAS) establishes himself in Hart's (NYK) path, Hart initiates lower-body contact, which affects Porzingis' SQBR during the pick.
Avdija (WAS) momentarily rests his hand on Robinson's (NYK) side as he is moving underneath the pick.
Robinson (NYK) establishes himself in Avdija's (WAS) path and absorbs the contact during the pick.
Randle (NYK) gathers the ball on his left foot and takes two legal steps before his shot attempt.
Beal (WAS) briefly rests his hand on Hart's (NYK) opposite hip as both players go for the loose ball.
Porzingis (WAS) is not in a legal vertical position as he is drawn toward Randle (NYK) when upper-body contact occurs, which affects his shot attempt near the basket.
Avdija (WAS) and Randle (NYK) come together as the pick is set. As Avdija is rolling toward the rim. he releases away without applying pressure.
Brunson (NYK) gathers the ball and slides his pivot foot before his shot attempt.
Avdija (WAS) rests his hand on Hart's (NYK) side and releases away without applying pressure as he rolls toward the rim.
Porzingis' (WAS) hand slides off Robinson's (NYK) arm after he retrieves the rebound, and the contact is marginal.

Kuzma (WAS) is moving to contest the layup attempt when marginal contact occurs with Robinson (NYK) on the layup attempt. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Kuzma's (WAS) right foot steps out of bounds as he receives the pass.
The timeout is assessed prior to any potential contact occurring between Morris (WAS) and Quickley (NYK).
Beal (WAS) slides his arm off Hart (NYK) as they engage and separate when Hart releases toward the perimeter.
Morris (WAS) commits a personal take foul on Quickley (NYK).
Grimes (NYK) avoids making contact with Kuzma (WAS) as he contests the shot attempt.
Morris (WAS) commits a take foul on Hart (NYK).
